tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired as indicated by elevated serum creatinine. Urinalysis shows proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible renal tubular dysfunction or chronic kidney disease. No evidence of urinary tract infection (negative nitrites, leukocytes, hemoglobin). Recommend further nephrological evaluation and monitoring of renal function.
